properties.headline: Wind Advisory issued February 2 at 6:11AM CST until February 2 at 3:00PM CST by NWS Duluth MN
properties.description:
...GUSTY WEST AND NORTHWEST WINDS THIS MORNING AND AFTERNOON...

.An area of low pressure will pass over the region this morning
and this afternoon. Strong west and northwest winds are expected
over central, east-central, and northeast Minnesota and northwest
Wisconsin this morning through this afternoon. Sustained winds of
10 to 25 mph are expected with gusts as high as 45 mph. Winds may
gust between 50 and 60 mph on the Bong and Blatnik bridges between
Duluth and Superior. The winds and gusts will weaken quickly this
afternoon as high pressure builds into the region.

* WHAT...Northwest winds 15 to 25 mph with gusts up to 40 mph.

* WHERE...North Itasca, Crow Wing, South Cass, Northern Aitkin,
South Aitkin, South Itasca and North Cass Counties. This
includes the Tribal Lands of the Bois Forte Band, Deer Creek
area and the Mille Lacs Band, East Lake and, Big Sandy Lake
areas.

* WHEN...Until 3 PM CST this afternoon.

* IMPACTS...Gusty winds could blow around unsecured objects.
Tree limbs could be blown down and a few power outages may
result.
properties.instruction:
Use extra caution when driving, especially if operating a high
profile vehicle. Secure outdoor objects.

NWSheadline: WIND ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 3 PM CST THIS AFTERNOON
